definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  all-trans-geranylgeranyl diphosphate -eq- ent-copalyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the oxidation of ubiquinol by diverting electrons from the standard electron transfer chain, transferring them from ubiquinol to oxygen and generating water as the product.
Catalysis of the removal of a C-5 double bond in the B ring of a sterol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-dehydroepisterol -eq- 24-methylenecholesterol.
The protein complex associated with the plasma membrane of certain plant cells (e.g. root cortex, epidermal cells) that functions to transport auxin out of the cell.
Catalysis of the reaction -  fatty acid (C-16 or longer) + 2-C -eq- fatty acid (C-16 or longer + 2-C).
A tetrameric complex of four different subunits which catalyzes the elongation of fatty acids chains 2 carbon units at a time in the synthesis of very long chain fatty acids.
Catalysis of the reaction -  octadecanal -eq- heptadecane + CO.

The region of the plasma membrane located at the basal end of the cell. Often used in reference to animal polarized epithelial membranes, where the basal membrane is the part attached to the extracellular matrix, or in plant cells, where the basal membrane is defined with respect to the zygotic axis.
Serves as a phospho-His intermediate enabling the transfer of phospho group between a hybrid kinase and a response regulator.
The side of the cell parallel to the zygotic axis.

Catalysis of the reactions -  ATP + a protein serine -eq- ADP + protein serine phosphate -  and ATP + a protein threonine -eq- ADP + protein threonine phosphate. These reactions are dependent on the presence of calcium ions.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an amino terminal propeptide, which functions as a sorting signal to sort away the soluble vacuolar protein from Golgi to lytic vacuole via clathrin-coated vesicles.
The double lipid bilayer enclosing the chloroplast and separating its contents from the rest of the cytoplasm -  includes the intermembrane space.
Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + sulfite + acceptor -eq- adenylyl sulfate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  zeinoxanthin + NADPH + O2 + H+ -eq- lutein + NADP+ + H2O. Adds a hydroxyl group to the epsilon ring of the alpha-carotene.
Catalysis of a ring closure reaction.

Catalysis of the reaction -  alkene group + alcohol group on same molecule -eq- cyclic ether. Substrates are 2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4- hydroquinone (forms delta-tocopherol) and 2,3-dimethyl-5-phytyl-1,4-hydroquinone (forms gamma-tocopherol).

label.value: proton motive force dependent protein transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of proteins from one side of the membrane to the other. Transportation is dependent on pH gradient across the membrane.
Catalysis of the reaction -  13(S)-hydroperoxylinolenate -eq- 12,13(S)-epoxylinolenate + H2O.
Catalysis of the introduction of an omega-3 double bond into an unsaturated 16-carbon fatty acid in a monogalactosyldiacylglycerol molecule.
Catalysis of the reaction -  RNA uridine -eq- RNA pseudouridine. Conversion of uridine in an RNA molecule to pseudouridine by rotation of the C1'-N-1 glycosidic bond of uridine in RNA to a C1'-C5.
The external part of the cell wall and|or plasma membrane.

label.value: cortical microtubule, transverse to long axis

definition.value: Arrays of microtubules underlying and connected to the plasma membrane, in the cortical cytosol, oriented mainly with their axes transverse to the long axis of the cell (and root in plants). In plants it influences the direction of cellulose microfibril deposition.
Protein translocon complex at the chloroplast outer membrane.
A heterotrimeric enzyme complex composed of three subunits, all of which are required for enzyme activity, which catalyzes the chelation of Mg by proto IX in an ATP-dependent manner.
The lipid bilayer surrounding an endosome.
The side (leaflet) of the endosome membrane that faces the cytoplasm.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with auxin, plant hormones that regulate aspects of plant growth.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-alpha-campestanaol + O2 -eq- 6-deoxocathasterone + H2O.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with N-1-naphthylphthalamic acid, an auxin transport inhibitor.

A novel compartment found in plant cells that is derived from the ER. The structures have a characteristic shape and size (10 mm long and 0.5 mm wide) and are surrounded with ribosomes. They have been found in Arabidopsis thaliana and related Brassicaceae species.

A large (200-800 kDa) multiprotein complex formed by 70-kDa and 5-kDa myrosinases, myrosinase- binding proteins (MBPs), MBP-related proteins and myrosinase-associated proteins. The complex has been identified in Brassica napus seeds.

Complex that catalyzes the synthesis of ADP-glucose and pyrophosphate from glucose-1-phosphate and ATP. In plants, the complex is a heterotetramer composed of two types of subunits (small and large). In bacteria, the enzyme complex is composed of four identical subunits.

label.value: nucleoside transmembrane transporter activity, against a concentration gradient

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a nucleoside, from one side of a membrane to the other, up a concentration gradient.
Catalysis of the transfer of amino alcohol sphingosine from one side of the membrane to the other.

Catalysis of the reaction -  homogentisate + phytyl diphosphate + H+ -eq- 2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4-benzoquinone + CO2 + diphosphate. 2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4-benzoquinone is also known as 2-methyl-6-phytylplastoquinol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxo-4-methylthiobutanoate + acetyl-CoA + H2O -eq- 2-(2'-methylthio)ethylmalic-acid + coenzyme A + H+.
Catalysis of the cleavage of the amide bond between IAA (auxin) and the conjugated amino acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-acetyl-alanine + H2O -eq- indole-3-acetate + L-alanine.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the enzyme thioglucosidase.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with FMN, flavin mononucleotide, the coenzyme or the prosthetic group of various flavoprotein oxidoreductase enzymes.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a vacuolar sorting signal, a specific peptide sequence that acts as a signal to localize the protein within the vacuole.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-acetyl-phenylalanine + H2O -eq- indole-3-acetate + phenylalanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  indole-3-acetyl-leucine + H2O -eq- indole-3-acetate + L-leucine.

Complex that carries out the oxidative decarboxylation of pyruvate to form acetyl-CoA -  comprises subunits possessing three catalytic activities -  pyruvate dehydrogenase (E1), dihydrolipoamide S-acetyltransferase (E2), and dihydrolipoamide dehydrogenase (E3). This complex is found in plant plastids and is distinct from the one found in mitochondria.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2 H2O -eq- O2 + 4 H+ + 4 e-. The evolution of oxygen from oxidizing water is carried out by the oxygen evolving complex in photosystem II of plants. P680+, the photochemically oxidized reaction-center chlorophyll of PSII, is a strong biological oxidant. The reduction potential of P680+ is more positive than that of water, and thus it can oxidize water to give O2 and H+ ions. The oxygen escapes as a gas while the H+ ions remain in solution inside the thylakoid vesicle.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phytol + CTP -eq- phytyl monophosphate + CDP + H+.
Catalysis of the reactions -  chlorophyllide a + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- 7-hydroxychlorophyllide a + H2O + NADP+ -  and 7-hydroxychlorophyllide a + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- chlorophyllide b + 2 H2O + NADP+.

The protein transport machinery of the chloroplast outer membrane that contains at least three components Toc159, Toc75 and Toc34, interacts with precursor proteins which are imported into the chloroplast in a GTP dependant manner.
